Log into MySQL from command line, using a password (it will prompt for the password):
$> mysql -u root -p

List the databases
$> show databases;

Use a specific database
$> use DBASENAME;

MySQL dump
This will prompt you for a password after hitting enter. The file will be created in the pwd:
mysqldump --all-databases --single-transaction --user=username --password > filename.sql

Run an *.sql file:
1. From the command line, navigate to the directory of the file.
2. Log into the mysql server (using the command above)
3. >source filename.sql
